About this item

  • TRAIL 2-PERSON DOME TENT WITH PORCH: Lightweight to carry and easy to pitch, the Bracken 2 Man Tent With Porch is a top choice for weekend camping and festival trips. It has a front porch to store equipment and space to sleep two people. Plus, an exclusive Dark Zone Bedroom to significantly block out sunlight and enjoy a longer, more relaxing sleep.
  • EXCEPTIONAL RAIN PROTECTION: The Bracken has a double-skin design with a 190T polyester flysheet and breathable inner sheet. With watertight taped seams and a Hydrostatic Head of 3000mm, it provides excellent protection from all but the heaviest of showers and is perfect for camping over the spring, summer, and early autumn months.
  • EXCLUSIVE DARK ZONE BEDROOM: Dark Zone Bedroom blocks out up to 70% more light than older models to enhance the quality and length of your sleep. The technology also allows the tent to absorb less sunlight which helps to keep it cooler in warmer weather. Vents with removable curtains on the roof and door allow you to let light in when needed.
  • FRONT PORCH TO STORE MUDDY EQUIPMENT: Been on a hike or rolling in the mud at a music festival? Keep the bedroom clean by storing your muddy boots in the porch area which has a roll down door with fasteners to keep your belongings dry and a vent to reduce condensation. Unlike the bedroom area, the porch doesn’t have a sewn-in groundsheet.
  • LIGHT TO CARRY, EASY TO PITCH: The Bracken is easy to pitch with three fibreglass poles, pre-attached hi-vis guy lines, steel pegs, and instructions. An oversized bag allows you to easily pack it away. When packed inside the bag, it weighs 3kg with handle to comfortably carry. When pitched, it measures L300cm x W140cm x H110cm (approx.).

    Product Description

    Bracken 2 Man Tent with Porch

    What you need to know!
    • Easy to pitch with sewn-in groundsheet
    • Waterproof (3000mm Hydrostatic Head)
    • 2-3 person ‘Dark Zone’ bedroom
    • Porch storage area (no groundsheet)
    • Oversized bag to easily store and carry
    • Bedroom: L200cm x W140cm x H100cm
    • Size of porch: L100cm x W140cm x H110cm
    • Weight: 3kg (when stored inside bag)
    2 Person Tent With Porch & Dark Zone Bedroom

    • Easy to pitch and perfect for short trips and festivals, our Bracken 2 Man Tent features a front porch to store your gear and a ‘Dark Zone’ bedroom to block out sunlight.
    • Extra features include a hook to hang a lantern and a mesh vent to aid ventilation. The bedroom and porch area also have separate zipper doors for easy customisation.

    Dome-Shaped for Strength & Wind-Resistance

    • Because the Bracken is a dome tent with poles that cross in the middle, it’s stronger, sturdier, and more wind-resistant than tunnel-shaped tents and other types.
    • The Bracken has a double skin design for enhanced rain protection, plus a sewn-in bedroom groundsheet to keep you sealed off from damp, draughts, and insects.

    Exclusive ‘Dark Zone’ Bedroom

    We’ve designed the bedroom with a ‘Dark Zone’ fabric liner which blocks out up to 70% more sunlight than regular fabric. As a result, it helps you to enjoy a longer, more relaxing sleep.

    Excellent Rain Protection

    Sudden downpours are no concern for the Bracken. With durable watertight taped seams and a 3000mm Hydrostatic Head (waterproof rating), it provides exceptional rain protection.

    Front Porch Storage Area

    The Bracken has a front porch to store your muddy boots and equipment. Unlike the bedroom area, it doesn’t have a sewn-in groundsheet, so there’s no need to worry about cleaning it out.

    Oversized Travel Bag Included

    The 2 person tent includes an oversized bag to easily pack and store away. When stored inside the bag, it measures 67cm x 15cm x 15cm and weighs 3kg with a handle to easily carry.

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings, help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      5.0 out of 5 stars Very good under the rain and high winds, contrary to some reviews
      Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 8 September 2024
      Verified Purchase
      This was bought for a summer camp for a teenager, and that week was very rainy and windy. The tent resisted very well, totally dry inside. The number of pegs was totally appropriate for use, contrary to what is mentioned in some reviews. You have to use the same peg for the inner cover and the outer cover, as written in the instructions, which are quite clear and easy to understand. If doing this, there is the correct number of pegs. One peg was quite bent in the pack when it arrived, but it was easy to put back into (straight) shape. The carry-bag for the tent quite big and it is easy to put the tent back in after use, contrary to some other tents we've had. It is good to have the help of one other person to fit the long poles into the holes of the cover, but otherwise it is easy to set up. Very happy with this tent.

      Solid tent and easy to put up. Rainproof and sturdy in high winds if erected and pegged correctly. Tent pegs it comes with are flimsy, you will need to buy proper ones. Front porch is also very lightweight and I often had to reconstruct it.

      In terms of size, this really is one of the smallest tents out there. I'm 6ft and could not lie down in it fully. Overall, a solid tent for a few days, but if you have the extra cash then I'd recommend going with another model.
